Nigeria’s Acting President, Prof. Yemi Osinbajo has directed the termination of the appointment of the Director General of the DSS, Mr. Lawal Musa Daura. Mr. Daura has been directed by the Ag. President to hand over the agency to the most senior officer of the State Security Service until further notice. More Details Later… Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. Produces when not on Social media.